The paper discusses a new class of rowhammer attacks that cross privilege boundaries, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the abuse of hardware and software features, which could fall under the categories of computer architecture (cs.AR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed attack also involves accessing and manipulating memory, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
